@startuml
actor Lecturer
participant "GradeController" as Controller
participant "GradeService" as GradeService
participant "AuditService" as Audit
participant "ICryptoService" as Crypto
database DB
actor Student
actor Admin

 Lecturer -> Controller : POST /api/submissions/{submissionId}/grade or PUT /api/grades/{gradeId}\ncredentialed cookie request
Controller -> GradeService : validate role + request
GradeService -> DB : load submission / grade
DB --> GradeService : submission / grade state
GradeService -> GradeService : ensure submission is VERIFIED\n(recommended rule)
GradeService -> DB : create or update Grade
GradeService -> Audit : record grade-sensitive action
Audit -> Audit : build canonical audit payload
Audit -> DB : load previousIntegrityValue (optional)
DB --> Audit : previousIntegrityValue
Audit -> Crypto : computeAuditMac(payload + previousIntegrityValue, auditSecret)
Crypto --> Audit : integrityValue (HMAC-SHA-256)
Audit -> DB : append AuditLog with integrityValue
DB --> Audit : audit stored
GradeService --> Controller : grade response
Controller --> Lecturer : 200/201 success

 Student -> Controller : GET /api/my/grades/{gradeId}\ncredentialed cookie request
Controller -> GradeService : authorise ownership + read grade
GradeService -> DB : load grade for owning student
DB --> GradeService : grade
GradeService --> Controller : grade
Controller --> Student : grade response

 Admin -> DB : inspect grade-related audit history through repository/database review
 DB --> Admin : audit trail for review/investigation

note right of GradeService
Pack 05 recommends that grades be created or updated
only for verified submissions to keep the integrity
story consistent.
end note

note right of Audit
Every grade create/update action must write an
append-oriented audit record protected with HMAC-SHA-256.
end note

note over Lecturer,Controller
In the implemented browser-facing contract, authentication
is carried by the backend-issued HttpOnly auth cookie.
An Authorization header may exist only as compatibility,
not as the primary frontend transport.
end note
@enduml

